A tanker spilled more than 10,000 tons of crude oil into the Yellow Sea Friday after being holed by a barge in what officials said was South Korea's worst oil spill.
A Hong Kong-registered oil tanker collided with another vessel in seas off South Korea's west coast Friday and leaked about 15,000 tons of crude oil, the Maritime and Fisheries Ministry said.
The previously largest oil spill in The South Korean government happened in 1995 when about 5,035 tons of crude and fuel oil was leaked, according to South Korea's Yonhap news agency.
